HEADWORD: Tridecatoic
<hw>Tri`dec*a*to"ic</hw>
<pr>(tr⟦isl⟧`d⟦ecr⟧k*⟦adot⟧*t⟦omac⟧"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Pref. <ets>tri-</ets> + Gr. <grk>de`katos</grk> tenth.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, that acid of
the fatty acids heterologous with tridecane. It is a white crystalline
substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

